docs.abstract: Salesforce is still in talks to buy Twitter, according to two people involved in the discussions, despite some of Salesforce’s largest shareholders indicating that they are against the deal.
docs.snippet: Salesforce is still in talks to buy Twitter, according to two people involved in the discussions, despite some of Salesforce’s largest shareholders indicating that they are against the deal.
docs.lead_paragraph: Even though some of the largest shareholders in Salesforce.com have made it clear that they are against the deal, the company is still in talks to buy Twitter, according to two people involved in the discussions who spoke on the condition of anonymity.

headline.main: Morning Agenda: Twitter-Salesforce Talks, Buffett’s Taxes, H.R. Red Flags

docs.abstract: The tech world has been buzzing since it heard that the online software company Salesforce was interested in bidding for Twitter.
docs.snippet: The tech world has been buzzing since it heard that the online software company Salesforce was interested in bidding for Twitter.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Marc Benioff, the founder and chief executive of Salesforce.com, showed up onstage on Wednesday afternoon at his biggest customer event of the year to talk up his business technology company’s products and strategy.

headline.main: Twitter’s Fate: Marc Benioff of Salesforce Addresses Acquisition Talk

docs.abstract: Theranos was recently a star of Silicon Valley. But now, it is closing its laboratory operations, shutting its wellness centers and laying off 340 employees.

docs.lead_paragraph: Not long ago, Theranos and its founder, Elizabeth Holmes, were stars of Silicon Valley.

docs.abstract: “While I look at a lot of things, I actually pass on most things,” Marc Benioff said after CNBC's Jim Cramer asked him to deny that his company would buy Twitter.
